                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Determine whether a linked list contains a cycle. Use Floyd's tortoise-and-hare algorithm: advance one pointer by 1 step and another by 2 steps; if they ever meet, a cycle exists. The algorithm uses O(1) extra space and works without modifying node values."
